OL,6,FCommunity matrons and district nurses
OL,7,Fvisiting patients in their homes should
OL,8,Fbe an ideal antidote to the NHS crisis.
OL,9,FThey can help people avoid becoming
OL,10,Ftrapped in overcrowded hospitals by
OL,11,Fspotting and treating illnesses at
OL,12,Fearly stages. When patients come out of
OL,13,Fhospital, they can monitor them and
OL,14,Foffer reassurance, while making certain
OL,15,Fthey receive the social care they need,
OL,16,Fso they aren't quickly calling 999
OL,17,Fagain.
OL,3,CCommunity nurses should help fix the
OL,4,CNHS crisis - but they're in crisis too
